description: Back formation from annals, borrowed from Middle French, from Latin annales (“annals”), from annus (“year”).

entries.meaning: The record of a single event or item.
examples: 1805,  Edward Young,  The Poetical Works of the Reverend Dr. Ed. Young: with the life of the author‎[1], volume 3, →ISBN:In deathless annal! deathless deeds inspire:
